This paper is about conversational agents and their training using data-driven methods. The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems. The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as conversational agents are a subset of AI. The third likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as data-driven methods are used for training conversational agents. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the societal impact of conversational agents. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper discusses the comparison of data from different corpora.
